05/03/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer, along with heads of state and prime ministers of about 30 countries, attended Friday's (5 March) funeral for Macedonian President Boris Trajkovski, who was killed a week ago in a plane crash. 
European Commission President Romano Prodi was to deliver a eulogy. 
On Thursday, thousands of Macedonians lined up to pay their last respects at parliament, where Trajkovski lay in state. 
(RFE/RL, VOA, AFP - 04/03/04)
